### Homework 2: Ticketing API Demo Requests
### Base URL: http://localhost:5002
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5002/api

### 1. Create a new ticket (manual classification)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Login page not loading",
  "description": "When I try to access the login page, I get a blank screen",
  "customerName": "John Doe",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "priority": "High",
  "category": "Technical"
}

### 2. Create a new ticket with auto-classification
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "URGENT: Payment failed need refund immediately",
  "description": "My credit card was charged but the payment shows as failed. Need refund ASAP",
  "customerName": "Jane Smith",
  "customerEmail": "jane.smith@company.com",
  "autoClassify": true
}

### 3. Get all tickets
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets

### 4. Get tickets by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?status=Open

### 5. Get tickets by priority
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?priority=Critical

### 6. Get tickets by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?category=Billing

### 7. Get tickets with multiple filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?status=Open&priority=High&category=Technical

### 8. Get a specific ticket by ID (change ID to match a created ticket)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets/1

### 9. Update a ticket
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "InProgress",
  "assignedTo": "Support Agent 1"
}

### 10. Auto-classify an existing ticket
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/1/auto-classify

### 11. Mark ticket as resolved
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Resolved"
}

### 12. Delete a ticket
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tickets/1

### 13. Import tickets from CSV
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

< ./sample_tickets.csv
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### 14. Import tickets from JSON
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.json"
Content-Type: application/json

< ./sample_tickets.json
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### 15. Import tickets from XML
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample_tickets.xml"
Content-Type: application/xml

< ./sample_tickets.xml
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### 16. Create ticket with validation error (invalid email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Test ticket",
  "description": "Testing validation",
  "customerName": "Test User",
  "customerEmail": "not-an-email"
}

### 17. Create ticket with validation error (subject too long)
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "This subject is intentionally made extremely long to exceed the 200 character limit and trigger a validation error. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam.",
  "description": "Testing validation",
  "customerName": "Test User",
  "customerEmail": "test@example.com"
}

### 18. Get tickets filtered by date range (last 7 days)
@sevenDaysAgo = {{$datetime 'iso8601' -7 d}}
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?fromDate={{sevenDaysAgo}}

### 19. Get tickets by customer email
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets?customerEmail=john.doe@example.com

### 20. Create multiple tickets for filtering demo
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Critical bug in production",
  "description": "Entire system is down affecting all users",
  "customerName": "Admin",
  "customerEmail": "admin@example.com",
  "priority": "Critical",
  "category": "Technical"
}
